ts. Instead, these bodies occupy the center of a global, highly financialized economy of creating and sustaining life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIntercountry adoptionzLatin America. 0aIntercountry adoptionzSouth Asia. 0aIntercountry adoption-Latin America. 0aIntercountry adoption-South Asia. 0aNannieszLatin America. 0aSurrogate motherhoodzSouth Asia. 0aSurrogate motherhood-South Asia. 0aWomen foreign workersxSocial conditions. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Science and Technology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aBanerjee, Anindita, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCastillo, Debra A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848108140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438481081423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438481081/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles